# React and TypeScript Development Guidelines

## Code Style
- Use early returns for better readability
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Prefix event handlers with "handle" (e.g., handleClick, handleKeyDown)
- Use const arrow functions instead of regular functions
- Define TypeScript types whenever possible

## Component Development
- Follow DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principles
- Implement proper accessibility features
  - Use tabindex="0" for interactive elements
  - Include aria-labels
  - Implement keyboard event handlers
- Use proper event handling patterns
- Leave no TODOs or placeholders
- Include all required imports

## State Management
- Use appropriate React hooks
- Implement proper state management patterns
- Handle side effects correctly

## TypeScript Best Practices
- Define proper interfaces and types
- Use TypeScript's type system effectively
- Avoid using 'any' type
- Leverage TypeScript's built-in utility types

## Error Handling
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use try-catch blocks where appropriate
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Handle edge cases appropriately